WEBVTT

00:03.130 --> 00:04.768
- You're quite the topic
of conversation

00:04.800 --> 00:08.133
in the psychiatric circles.
The reason you failed to
capture the Chesapeake Ripper

00:08.170 --> 00:10.604
is I already had him.
- I did it.

00:10.640 --> 00:14.030
- Miriam Lass is dead.
The Chesapeake Ripper is making
it very clear that someone is

00:14.080 --> 00:16.742
plagiarizing his work.
- Is it possible you

00:16.780 --> 00:20.443
inadvertently planted
the suggestion in Gideon's mind

00:20.480 --> 00:22.687
that he was the Ripper?
- Psychic driving is unethical.

00:22.720 --> 00:26.315
- I have feelings for you.
I can't just have an affair.
- Why?

00:26.360 --> 00:29.750
- I think you're unstable.
- You're the subject of a lot
of speculation at the bureau.

00:29.790 --> 00:32.793
Jack pushed you right up
to the edge and now you're
pushing yourself over.

00:32.830 --> 00:36.288
- (Jack): What happened
in there? I saw the look
on your face.

00:36.330 --> 00:39.697
- You must overcome
these delusions that_are
dingIsmg your reality.

00:39.740 --> 00:42.334
- It's anti-NMDA receptor
encephalitis.

00:42.370 --> 00:45.737
- Now that we have confirmed
what it is, it'll be easier
to hide from him.

00:49.180 --> 00:52.274
Someone who already doubts
their own identity

00:52.320 --> 00:54.515
can be more susceptible
to manipulation.

00:54.550 --> 00:56.780
Dr. Gideon is a psychopath.

00:56.820 --> 01:00.256
Psychopaths are narcissists.
They rarely doubt who they are.

01:00.290 --> 01:03.782
- I tried to appeal
to his narcissism.

01:03.830 --> 01:06.697
- By convincing him
he was the Chesapeake Ripper.

01:09.530 --> 01:11.521
- If only I had been
more curious

01:11.570 --> 01:14.095
about the common mind.
- I have

01:14.140 --> 01:18.429
no interest in understanding
sheep; only eating them.

01:18.470 --> 01:23.203
Kudal. A South Indian curry.

01:23.250 --> 01:25.548
Made from sheep, of course.

01:25.580 --> 01:28.617
In a coconut-coriander-
chIII sauce.

01:31.290 --> 01:33.850
- It feels like a last supper.

01:33.890 --> 01:37.849
- You're not the only
psychiatrist accused by
a patient of making them kill.

01:37.890 --> 01:40.791
Poke around a psychopath's mind,

01:40.830 --> 01:44.322
bound to get poked back.

01:46.340 --> 01:48.558
- What would you do
in my position?

01:48.600 --> 01:51.535
- Deny everything.

01:53.540 --> 01:56.600
- I thought psychic driving
would have been more effective
in breaking down

01:56.650 --> 02:00.177
his personality.
- Psychic driving fails
because its methods are

02:00.220 --> 02:04.384
too obvious. You were trying
too hard, Frederick.
If force is used,

02:04.420 --> 02:07.856
the subject will only surrender
temporarily. Once a patient is
exposed

02:07.890 --> 02:10.927
to the method of manipulation,
it becomes much less effective.

02:10.960 --> 02:13.394
- When Dr. Gideon began

02:13.430 --> 02:16.820
to suspect he was being pushed--
- He pushed back.

02:16.870 --> 02:20.260
The subject mustn't be aware
of any influence.

02:20.300 --> 02:22.302
(insects chirping)

03:13.990 --> 03:17.585
(breathing rapidly)

03:48.560 --> 03:50.619
(startled shouting)

03:53.600 --> 03:55.750
(catching his breath)

04:06.340 --> 04:09.468
- So, you get to dress up
and I don't?

04:09.510 --> 04:11.478
This might affect how well

04:11.510 --> 04:13.717
my testimony goes over
with the judge.

04:13.750 --> 04:16.947
- Testimony speaks for itself.
- Frederick, don't look
so worried.

04:16.990 --> 04:20.312
I forgive you your trespasses.
- What trespasses are those?

04:20.360 --> 04:22.521
- You made me
kill the nurse.

04:22.560 --> 04:25.427
I take responsibility for
killing my wife and her family.

04:25.460 --> 04:27.451
The nurse is your fault.
- I cannot

04:27.500 --> 04:29.718
accept responsibility
for your actions, Abel.

04:29.770 --> 04:32.864
- Au contraire.
It's why I'm suing you.

04:32.900 --> 04:35.869
You made me think I was
somebody else,

04:35.900 --> 04:37.868
and now...

04:37.910 --> 04:40.674
who knows what I'm thinking?
- Dr. Gideon,

04:40.710 --> 04:44.703
you told me you were
the Chesapeake Ripper.
- Dr. Chilton, you told

04:44.750 --> 04:50.848
me I was the Chesapeake Ripper,
and that's what I'm going
to tell everyone.

04:50.890 --> 04:53.484
- See you in court.

05:16.780 --> 05:18.372
- You married?

05:20.880 --> 05:22.882
You married?

05:24.890 --> 05:26.858
You're married.

05:26.890 --> 05:29.984
How long you married?

05:30.030 --> 05:31.759
That long?

05:34.160 --> 05:38.859
Regarding divorce--
not that you're getting one;

05:38.900 --> 05:44.008
just I can see the clock
in your eyes--

05:44.040 --> 05:46.008
word of advice:

05:46.040 --> 05:49.601
it's easier just
to kill 'em.

05:49.650 --> 05:51.868
Kill 'em, kill everyone
at the table.

05:51.910 --> 05:53.946
Less paperwork.

05:53.980 --> 05:57.586
Worked for me.
I'm doing OK.

05:57.620 --> 06:01.078
Your wife is
probably fantastic.

06:01.120 --> 06:04.021
My wife? Horrible.

06:04.060 --> 06:06.449
So maybe I'm not supposed
to be in a relationship.

06:06.500 --> 06:07.899
There's people like that.

06:10.730 --> 06:13.699
How do you keep those whites
so clean? That's...

06:13.740 --> 06:15.594
Always amazes me.

06:30.450 --> 06:33.749
***

