08:05.780 --> 08:09.238
- All I need is one hand free.

08:27.740 --> 08:29.139
(neck snapping)

08:36.910 --> 08:39.242
(man yelling)

08:43.350 --> 08:46.558
(Will breathing rapidly)

09:04.070 --> 09:06.038
- So, does Abel Gideon
still believe that he's

09:06.070 --> 09:08.038
the Chesapeake Ripper?

09:08.080 --> 09:10.173
- Abel Gideon is having

09:10.210 --> 09:12.849
a difference of opinion
about who he is.

09:32.400 --> 09:34.265
The man who escaped

09:34.300 --> 09:37.599
from that van was not
in the same state of mind

09:37.640 --> 09:40.200
when he did this.

09:40.240 --> 09:42.606
- He took a uniform,
police radio,

09:42.650 --> 09:45.869
two 9mm handguns, pepper spray,
Taser, and handcuffs.

09:45.910 --> 09:48.276
- Well, it's what
he didn't take.

09:48.320 --> 09:49.878
- (Bev): He hung the organs

09:49.920 --> 09:51.888
from the branch with vein
from the victims.

09:51.920 --> 09:53.888
- He even tied little bows
with some of them.

09:53.920 --> 09:55.888
- Yeah, it's really impressive.

09:55.920 --> 09:59.253
- The Chesapeake Ripper would
not have left the organs behind.

09:59.290 --> 10:03.090
- Well, if Gideon isn't
the Chesapeake Ripper,

10:03.130 --> 10:04.995
he's certainly trying
to get his attention.

10:05.030 --> 10:07.828
- Local PD picked up
a foot trail leading

10:07.870 --> 10:10.065
out of the woods. Boot soles are
consistent with the ones

10:10.110 --> 10:12.066
we found at the crime scene.
- How fresh are the tracks?

10:12.110 --> 10:14.829
- Two, three hours old.
- Which direction they headed?

10:14.880 --> 10:16.939
- Back to Baltimore.

10:16.980 --> 10:19.073
(Jack sighs.)

10:22.820 --> 10:24.811
(door opening)

10:24.850 --> 10:27.387
- I suppose this is
my fault too?

10:29.760 --> 10:32.388
- You did dodge a bullet.

10:32.430 --> 10:34.990
Gideon's escape foregoes a trial

10:35.030 --> 10:38.067
and a very public humiliation
for you.

10:38.100 --> 10:40.762
- And now you are hosting
a private one.

10:40.800 --> 10:42.768
Next you'll be accusing me

10:42.810 --> 10:45.028
of arranging his escape.
- No one's making

10:45.070 --> 10:47.334
that accusation.
- If we're tossmg around

10:47.380 --> 10:49.974
the blame, Dr. Bloom,
you're due your fair share.

10:50.010 --> 10:53.377
You planted the idea that I was
unethically manipulating Gideon.

10:53.420 --> 10:55.376
- Well, according to Gideon,
you were.

10:55.420 --> 10:58.685
- After you told him I was.
You thought I was manipulating

10:58.720 --> 11:01.154
him? He was manipulating you.

11:01.190 --> 11:04.421
- You were pushing him.
- He gave me informed
consent to treat him,

11:04.460 --> 11:09.124
said that he was grateful
for my help

11:09.160 --> 11:11.822
in understanding who he is.
- What did you help him

11:11.870 --> 11:15.169
understand?
- He was not Insane

11:15.200 --> 11:17.930
when he killed his wife;
killing her drove him insane.

11:17.970 --> 11:20.734
I did not convince him
that he was a serial killer;

11:20.780 --> 11:22.975
I just reminded him of the fact.

11:23.010 --> 11:25.376
- Gideon is not
the Chesapeake Ripper,

11:25.410 --> 11:28.846
although he might have thought
he was under your care, Doctor.

11:28.880 --> 11:31.087
- Whether he is or he isn't
doesn't really matter

11:31.120 --> 11:34.009
right now. If he thinks he is
or even if he's confused

11:34.060 --> 11:37.029
