he will kill again.
- I hope he does not,

11:37.060 --> 11:39.483
I mean for your sake.
Cannot imagine

11:39.530 --> 11:42.499
how you would sleep
with that on your shoulders.

11:42.530 --> 11:46.830
(Chilton's voice distant)
During those three minutes,
Gideon did horrible things.

11:46.870 --> 11:48.963
- How did you sleep
when Gideon killed your nurse?

11:50.940 --> 11:52.931
- What does Gideon want?

11:52.980 --> 11:55.778
- The last thing Abel Gideon
said to me is that he intends

11:55.810 --> 11:59.439
to tell everyone that he is
the Chesapeake Ripper.

12:02.990 --> 12:05.948
- Our fugitive is Abel Gideon.
Transplant surgeon.

12:05.990 --> 12:07.412
Convicted in the first degree

12:07.460 --> 12:10.452
in the murders of his wife
and her family.

12:10.490 --> 12:14.324
Institutionalized at the
Baltimore State Hospital
for the Criminally Insane,

12:14.360 --> 12:16.828
where he killed a nurse
and claimed to be

12:16.870 --> 12:18.826
the Chesapeake Ripper.
(Jack's voice becoming distant)

12:18.870 --> 12:21.839
Dr. Gideon escaped this morning
after killing three people.

12:21.870 --> 12:24.964
He is armed and dangerous. He is
believed to be...

12:25.010 --> 12:27.069
(Jack's voice echoing)
...in the first degree

12:27.110 --> 12:31.103
in the murders of his wife and
her family. Institutionalized

12:31.150 --> 12:36.941
at the Baltimore State Hospital
for the Criminally Insane.

12:36.990 --> 12:38.343
Insane.

12:38.390 --> 12:41.018
(Jack's voice distant)
...escaped this morning.

12:41.060 --> 12:45.224
He is armed, he is dangerous...
You escaped this morning.

12:45.260 --> 12:47.194
He escaped this morning.
He is armed and he is

12:47.230 --> 12:49.960
extremely dangerous.
You escaped this morning.

12:50.000 --> 12:53.436
Institutionalized
at the Baltimore State...
(cacophony of Jack's vorce)

12:53.470 --> 12:56.962
What kind of crazy are you?!

12:57.010 --> 13:01.071
You kill! You will kill again!
(Jack's voice echoing)

13:14.620 --> 13:16.554
(Jack speaking indistinctly)

13:16.590 --> 13:19.957
(people murmuring quietly)

13:29.270 --> 13:32.034
- (Lecter): What did you see?

13:32.070 --> 13:34.072
- A thicket of antlers.

13:36.910 --> 13:40.016
All I heard was my heart,

13:40.050 --> 13:44.214
dim but... but fast,

13:44.250 --> 13:47.549
like, um... footsteps

13:47.590 --> 13:49.581
fleeing into silence.

13:53.100 --> 13:56.319
I don't know how to gauge
who I am anymore.

14:01.200 --> 14:04.328
gradually becoming different
for a while.

14:04.370 --> 14:07.533
I just feel like somebody else.

14:07.580 --> 14:09.946
- What do you feel like?

14:14.020 --> 14:15.373
- I feel crazy.

14:15.420 --> 14:18.389
(Will breathing shakily)

14:18.420 --> 14:20.888
- And that is
what you fear most.

14:23.430 --> 14:25.887
- I fear not knowing who I am.

14:32.700 --> 14:35.897
That's what Abel Gideon's
afraid of, isn't it?

14:37.710 --> 14:39.564
He's like a blind man.

14:41.680 --> 14:45.104
Somebody got inside his head
and...

14:45.150 --> 14:48.608
moved all the furniture around.

14:48.650 --> 14:51.244
- I imagine Abel Gideon would
want to find

14:51.290 --> 14:54.509
the Chesapeake Ripper
to gauge who he is.

14:54.560 --> 14:56.687
And who he isn't.

14:56.720 --> 14:58.927
Will.

15:02.730 --> 15:04.925
You have me as your gauge.

15:12.170 --> 15:14.138
- Gideon didn't leave

15:14.180 --> 15:16.535
a manifesto. We confiscated
all correspondence

15:16.580 --> 15:19.549
from his outside admire_rs. We're
gomg through everything now.
- Good.

15:19.580 --> 15:23.311
- Any secret communiqus
or coded messages written
in bodily fluids

15:23.350 --> 15:25.545
or anything else,
we'll find them.

15:25.590 --> 15:27.285
- You won't find anything.

15:27.320 --> 15:29.117
Whatever's going on

15:29.160 --> 15:30.559
with Gideon, it's in his head.

15:30.590 --> 15:32.956
- Well, there's not much left
in these heads.

15:33.000 --> 15:36.652
All organ removal was done
postmortem, including the
transorbital lobotomies.

15:36.700 --> 15:39.294
- It wasn't technically
a lobotomy.

15:39.330 --> 15:42.265
He didn't remove
any of the brain;
he just scrambled them.

15:42.300 --> 15:45.303
Went in through the top
of the eye socket...

16:00.320 --> 16:03.221
- (Jack): OK, OK.
Tell me something.

16:03.260 --> 16:06.525
Why remove
all of the other organs

16:06.560 --> 16:09.358
from the bodies
and leave them intact

16:09.400 --> 16:11.322
and just scramble the brains?

16:11.370 --> 16:14.430
- That's what they did to him.

16:14.470 --> 16:16.461
- That's what who did to him?

16:16.500 --> 16:19.469
- Dr. Chilton, every
psychiatrist and PhD candidate

16:19.510 --> 16:21.478
who attempted any kind
of therapy,

16:21.510 --> 16:23.444
pushed and prodded,
gave him tests, told him

16:23.480 --> 16:25.072
who he was, who he wasn't.

16:25.110 --> 16:27.476
- All right. I want a list
of every therapist,

16:27.520 --> 16:30.318
every doctor, any kind
of psychiatric professional

16:30.350 --> 16:32.716
that worked with or talked to
Dr. Gideon.

16:34.720 --> 16:37.052
- Alana Bloom will be
on that list.

16:44.400 --> 16:46.288
- Are you my protective custody?

16:46.330 --> 16:48.161
- You heard?

16:48.200 --> 16:51.704
- I heard I get an armed escort
until Gideon's apprehended.

16:51.740 --> 16:53.708
- You'll have a real FBI agent,

16:53.740 --> 16:56.379
_ not a teacher
With a temporary badge.

16:56.410 --> 16:59.675
- Too bad. Would have been fun

16:59.710 --> 17:02.713
to cozy up with your dogs
in front of a space heater.

17:02.750 --> 17:06.686
- You don't need protective
custody to cozy up with my dogs.

17:08.690 --> 17:10.658
Or me, for that matter.

17:13.660 --> 17:16.220
Just need a little more, um...

17:16.260 --> 17:19.423
stability on my part.

17:26.710 --> 17:30.305
- You're really warm.

17:30.350 --> 17:32.341
- Yeah, I tend to run hot.

17:35.180 --> 17:38.547
They say stress raises
body temperature.

17:38.590 --> 17:41.514
- Maybe you should take
an aspirin.

17:41.560 --> 17:44.529
- Way ahead of you.

17:44.560 --> 17:48.348
- They're gonna kill Gideon,
aren't they?

17:52.370 --> 17:56.295
- Whatever happens to him has
nothing to do

17:56.340 --> 17:58.205
with you.
- Gideon can't be

17:58.240 --> 18:00.276
completely responsible
for his actions

18:00.310 --> 18:03.438
if he was subjected
to an outside influence.

18:03.480 --> 18:05.778
- What, like Chilton telling him
he's the Chesapeake Ripper?

18:05.810 --> 18:09.268
- Like me

18:09.320 --> 18:12.346
telling him he's not
in a state of mind
to know who he is.

18:14.360 --> 18:17.682
- Well, he's gonna want somebody
to tell him who he is,
and I think he'll be

18:17.730 --> 18:20.654
looking for the Ripper
to do that.

18:23.930 --> 18:27.468
- What do you think will
happen if Gideon finds
the Chesapeake Ripper?

18:29.470 --> 18:31.609
- The Chesapeake Ripper will
kill him.

18:33.610 --> 18:36.431
He took credit
for his work.

18:36.480 --> 18:40.143
The Ripper would
consider that rude.

18:44.220 --> 18:46.415
(cell phone ringtone)

18:54.360 --> 18:56.590
- Freddie Lounds.

18:56.630 --> 18:59.622
- Gideon: [My name is Paul
Carruthers. I'm a psychiatrist.]

18:59.670 --> 19:01.934
[I read your article
on Abel Gideon.]

19:01.970 --> 19:04.461
- And I yours, Dr. Carruthers.

19:04.510 --> 19:06.466
- [So you're aware of my work?]

19:06.510 --> 19:08.478
- I found your paper

19:08.510 --> 19:11.479
on narcissistic _
personality disorder in5ightful,

19:11.510 --> 19:14.616
Especially as it pertains
to your opinions of Abel Gideon.

19:14.650 --> 19:17.813
- [Well, thank you.
That's very kind of you.]

19:17.850 --> 19:19.818
- You're calling
about his escape?

19:19.850 --> 19:22.956
- [Well, yes. I'd like
to collaborate]

19:22.990 --> 19:26.289
