there's no need to patronize me.

22:57.040 --> 22:59.964
- I'm sorry.

23:03.010 --> 23:07.106
- It's like remembering
something from your childhood,

23:07.150 --> 23:09.710
and you're not sure

23:09.750 --> 23:13.459
if it's your memory,
or a friend's memory,

23:13.490 --> 23:18.029
and then you realize sadly it's
just some photo in an old book.

23:21.160 --> 23:23.128
- You're waiting

23:23.160 --> 23:25.822
for the Chesapeake Ripper
to come back here.

23:25.870 --> 23:29.988
- Let's hope
he gets the invitation.

23:30.040 --> 23:33.430
There's one thing we know
about your writing:

23:33.480 --> 23:36.131
he is an avid fan.

23:51.230 --> 23:53.186
- Dr. Carson Nahn.

23:53.230 --> 23:55.994
He's the psychiatric attending
at Western General.

23:56.030 --> 23:58.498
He interviewed Dr. Gideon

23:58.530 --> 24:00.896
for the same psychopathy survey
I participated in

24:00.940 --> 24:04.239
two years ago.
- Total frenectomy,
webbing under the tongue;

24:04.270 --> 24:08.104
even the connective tissue
all the way into the throat
is cut free and pulled through

24:08.140 --> 24:10.870
for the, uh, desired effect.

24:10.910 --> 24:12.468
(Jack sighs.)

24:12.510 --> 24:14.478
- Still no word
from Dr. Chilton?

24:14.520 --> 24:16.715
- He hasn't answered his phone
since yesterday,

24:16.750 --> 24:18.479
didn't show up to work today.

24:18.520 --> 24:20.659
- Gideon wants
to lure the Ripper.

24:20.690 --> 24:24.182
He's going to offer up the man
who disrespected both
their identities.

24:24.230 --> 24:27.529
- Every detail
of Dr. Carruthers' murder

24:27.560 --> 24:30.154
as described meticulously
in Freddie Lounds' article

24:30.200 --> 24:33.192
has been faithfully
reproduced except...

24:33.230 --> 24:35.494
for one.

24:35.540 --> 24:40.068
- What's different about Carson?
Why amputate his arm?

24:40.110 --> 24:42.704
- (Jack): Did Freddie write
anything about this?

24:42.740 --> 24:44.844
- (Brian): Not that I know of,
no.

24:44.880 --> 24:47.098
- Abel Gideon didn't kill
this man;

24:47.150 --> 24:49.243
the Chesapeake Ripper did.

24:49.280 --> 24:51.589
- You said
the Chesapeake Ripper

24:51.620 --> 24:55.989
would want to kill Gideon
for taking credit for his work.

24:56.020 --> 24:58.250
- Gideon isn't alone anymore,

24:58.290 --> 25:02.226
and the Ripper isn't going
to risk exposure,

25:02.260 --> 25:05.889
so, no, he's...
he's, um...

25:05.930 --> 25:09.661
he's telling us
where to catch him.

25:12.040 --> 25:14.008
Actually, he's telling you.

25:14.040 --> 25:16.531
- Me?

25:16.580 --> 25:19.105
- Where's the last place
you saw a severed arm, Jack?

25:28.060 --> 25:30.984
- With experience, I have found

25:31.030 --> 25:33.749
surgeries are best performed
on a local anesthetic

25:33.800 --> 25:37.588
or epidural
with the patient awake.

25:37.630 --> 25:41.589
Reminds me
there's a real person here
entrusting me with their life

25:41.640 --> 25:44.131
rather than a lump of meat
that I'm about to reorganize.

25:44.170 --> 25:46.866
And in this instance,

25:46.910 --> 25:49.276
I would like to see the look
on your face.

25:49.310 --> 25:52.347
- Please... You're not
the Chesapeake Ripper.

25:52.380 --> 25:54.871
- You got inside my mind,
Frederick.

25:54.920 --> 25:58.686
It's only fair
I get inside your belly.

25:58.720 --> 26:01.018
This is of course
Freddie Lounds, who you know.

26:01.060 --> 26:04.757
She will be assisting me today--
or assisting you--by manually
pumping the ventilator

26:04.790 --> 26:07.691
should you stop breathing.

26:07.730 --> 26:09.322
- Oh, my god.

26:16.800 --> 26:20.839
- The real Chesapeake Ripper is
a collector

26:20.880 --> 26:22.836
of surgical trophies.

26:22.880 --> 26:25.144
I'm gonna leave him
a little gift.

26:25.180 --> 26:27.740
In fact, I'm gonna leave him
a gift basket.

26:51.170 --> 26:54.139
You know, it is truly amazing

26:54.180 --> 26:58.640
how many organs the body can
offer up before it really
begins to suffer.

27:05.120 --> 27:08.248
All right, stay awake now!
Come on, Frederick.

27:08.290 --> 27:11.623
I'm gonna ask you
to hold a few things.

27:14.460 --> 27:16.758
Hmm. What next?

27:25.240 --> 27:27.834
- (Jack): I want you to wait
outside.

27:30.140 --> 27:31.949
- That's probably best.

27:31.980 --> 27:34.119
- You look like hell, Will.

27:34.150 --> 27:36.846
- I feel like hell.

27:36.880 --> 27:39.383
Actually, no, I feel...

27:39.420 --> 27:41.980
uh, fluid,

27:42.020 --> 27:45.023
like I'm spilling.

27:47.160 --> 27:49.355
Must have come down
with something.

27:49.400 --> 27:52.392
I hope it's not contagious.

27:52.430 --> 27:56.992
(Jack's voice distant)
- This work that we do...

27:57.040 --> 28:00.703
(Jack's voice normal)
...it will compromise your
immune system, if you allow it.

28:00.740 --> 28:03.868
You've got to keep things
in perspective. You've got
to keep yourself in perspective.

28:03.910 --> 28:06.378
- Well, myself is a little hazy
at the moment.

28:06.410 --> 28:09.447
- You've gotta start
taking better care of yourself.

28:09.480 --> 28:13.211
- Build my resistance?
- You just can't take it all in.

28:15.460 --> 28:18.759
You've got to let go
of as much of it as you can.

28:18.790 --> 28:22.294
You just gotta let go.
- You know, it's hard

28:22.330 --> 28:26.164
to shake off something
that's already under your skin.

29:04.240 --> 29:05.832
- Mark.

29:46.010 --> 29:47.409
Go!

29:55.490 --> 29:58.857
- Clear. Clear.
No sign of Gideon.

29:58.890 --> 30:01.029
- He's still alive.

30:01.060 --> 30:03.995
- I need medical in here now!

30:04.030 --> 30:06.089
- Gideon's gone.

30:44.970 --> 30:48.098
- I was expecting
the Chesapeake Ripper.

30:51.010 --> 30:53.001
Or are you he?

30:55.120 --> 30:57.418
- Turn around. Don't look at me.

31:03.460 --> 31:07.089
- You are looking
a little peaky,

31:07.130 --> 31:12.022
Mr. Graham,
if you don't mind my saying.

31:12.070 --> 31:15.335
Call me crazy, but you look ill.

31:15.370 --> 31:18.533
- Drive.

31:18.570 --> 31:21.004
- Who is your doctor?

31:30.450 --> 31:33.283
- I'm having a hard time
thinking.

31:33.320 --> 31:35.982
(Will panting)

31:36.020 --> 31:40.127
I feel like I'm losing my mind.
I-I don't know what's real.

31:44.530 --> 31:47.522
- It's 7:27 PM.

31:47.570 --> 31:51.609
You're in Baltimore, Maryland,
and your name is Will Graham.
- No I don't care who I am!

31:51.640 --> 31:54.234
Just tell me...

31:54.280 --> 31:56.134
if he's real.

32:02.320 --> 32:04.311
- Who do you see, Will?

32:06.550 --> 32:08.586
- Garret Jacob Hobbs.

32:08.620 --> 32:10.611
Who do you see?

32:17.030 --> 32:18.520
- I don't see anyone.

32:18.570 --> 32:20.492
- No, he's right there.

32:20.530 --> 32:22.498
- There's no one there, Will.
- No, no, you're lying.

32:22.540 --> 32:25.532
- We're alone.
You came here alone.
Do you remember coming here?

32:25.570 --> 32:28.209
- No, please don't lie to me!
- Garret Jacob Hobbs is dead.

32:28.240 --> 32:30.208
You killed him.
You watched him die.

32:30.240 --> 32:33.175
- What's happening to me?
- Will,

32:33.210 --> 32:35.713
Will, Will, you're having
an episode. I want you

32:35.750 --> 32:39.481
to hand me over the gun. Will,
I want you to hand me your...

32:39.520 --> 32:41.283
Will?

32:41.320 --> 32:42.719
Will.

33:08.620 --> 33:10.576
He's had a mild seizure.

33:10.620 --> 33:14.454
- That doesn't seem
to bother you.

33:16.560 --> 33:18.323
- I said it was mild.

33:23.630 --> 33:27.361
Are you the man who claimed
to be the Chesapeake Ripper?

33:27.400 --> 33:30.437
- Why do you say "claimed"?

33:30.470 --> 33:33.439
- Because you're not.
You know you're not,

33:33.470 --> 33:36.177
and you don't know much more
about who you are beyond that.

33:36.210 --> 33:39.179
- Are you the Ripper?

33:39.210 --> 33:41.747
- A terrible thing...

33:41.780 --> 33:44.783
to have your identity taken
from you.

33:47.450 --> 33:49.418
- Well, I'm taking it back,

33:49.460 --> 33:51.826
one piece at a time.

33:51.860 --> 33:55.523
You should see the pieces
I got out of my psychiatrist.

33:58.530 --> 34:01.499
- Alana Bloom was
one of your psychiatrists too.

34:01.540 --> 34:03.269
Is that right?

34:03.300 --> 34:07.134
- Yes. Dr. Bloom.

34:12.410 --> 34:14.571
- I can tell you
where to find her.

34:26.260 --> 34:27.784
Will, can you hear me?

34:32.270 --> 34:34.488
Repeat after me.

34:34.540 --> 34:37.498
My name is Will Graham.

34:37.540 --> 34:39.269
- My name is Will Graham.

34:42.880 --> 34:44.848
- Raise both of your arms.

34:44.880 --> 34:47.508
More.

34:47.550 --> 34:50.519
More.

34:50.550 --> 34:53.383
Good.

34:53.420 --> 34:56.412
Although you may not feel
like it, I need you to smile.

35:04.830 --> 35:08.129
Good. It wasn't a stroke.

35:08.170 --> 35:10.866
You may have had a seizure.

35:10.900 --> 35:13.164
Tell me the last thing
you remember.

35:13.210 --> 35:15.178
- I...

35:15.210 --> 35:17.599
(Will panting)

35:17.640 --> 35:19.642
I was
with Garret Jacob Hobbs.

35:25.650 --> 35:27.743
- You have a fever.

35:27.790 --> 35:30.657
You were hallucinating.
You thought he was alive,

35:30.690 --> 35:33.557
here in the room with you.
- I saw him.

35:33.590 --> 35:36.593
- He's a delusion
disguising reality.

35:36.630 --> 35:40.396
Don't let that
let you slip away.

35:40.430 --> 35:43.467
You killed
Garret Jacob Hobbs once.

35:43.500 --> 35:44.899
You can find

35:44.940 --> 35:47.135
a way to kill him again.

35:50.540 --> 35:52.576
- Where are you going?
- Abel Gideon is still

35:52.610 --> 35:54.714
at large.
He mutilated Dr. Chilton.

35:54.750 --> 35:57.639
They found him
clinging to life.

35:57.680 --> 35:59.784
I'm worried about Alana.

35:59.820 --> 36:03.756
- Alana. _
- No, no, no, no, no, no. Will.

36:03.790 --> 36:05.758
You're in no state to go

36:05.790 --> 36:08.759
anywhere but the hospital.
I'll call Jack

36:08.800 --> 36:10.756
and tell him where you are.

36:36.290 --> 36:38.485
- I have to make a phone call.
Can I ask you to step out?

37:14.700 --> 37:21.026
- I don't know if I will
ever be myself again.

37:21.070 --> 37:24.858
I don't know if I've got
any "self" left over.

37:24.910 --> 37:28.869
I spent so long
thinking I was him,

37:28.910 --> 37:33.802
it's gotten really hard
to remember who I was
when I wasn't him.

37:37.750 --> 37:41.015
- Who are you now?

37:41.050 --> 37:44.281
- Now I'm you.

37:44.330 --> 37:48.528
We're both here,
looking at her,

37:48.560 --> 37:52.690
just those kind of people that
shouldn't be in a relationship.

37:52.730 --> 37:56.939
You and I are
already committed.

37:56.970 --> 37:59.939
It's hard to be
with another person when you...

37:59.970 --> 38:03.599
can't get out
of your own head.

38:03.640 --> 38:06.404
- I want to get out.

38:06.450 --> 38:08.418
- Yeah, well,

38:08.450 --> 38:10.771
we all want things
that we can't have.

38:12.790 --> 38:14.781
But if I kill her

38:14.820 --> 38:18.426
like he would kill her,
then maybe

38:18.460 --> 38:22.089
I could
understand him better.

38:22.130 --> 38:26.863
I wonder if _then
you would finally
understand what you've become.

38:34.140 --> 38:36.370
(gunshot)

38:52.890 --> 38:55.597
- They will be sewing up

38:55.630 --> 38:57.598
Dr. Chilton until the morning--

38:57.630 --> 38:59.495
that is, if he makes it
through the night.

38:59.530 --> 39:02.533
- At least Will remains
in one piece--

39:02.570 --> 39:04.435
for now.

39:08.140 --> 39:10.836
His temperature is 105.

39:10.880 --> 39:13.599
White blood cell count is

39:13.650 --> 39:17.711
twice normal, and they still
can't identify the source
of his infection.

39:17.750 --> 39:21.516
- They will.

39:21.560 --> 39:23.516
- You seem confident.

39:23.560 --> 39:26.028
-Iam.

39:26.060 --> 39:29.154
Even with a temperature
of 105 degrees, Will was able

39:29.200 --> 39:32.499
to bring Gideon down.
I told you, he'll be fine.

39:32.530 --> 39:36.091
-Jack".

39:36.140 --> 39:39.860
I would recommend you suspend
his license to carry firearms.

39:39.910 --> 39:44.404
- You and I are just gonna have
to have a difference of opinion
about who Will is, Doctor.

39:44.450 --> 39:46.975
- I know who Will is.

39:47.010 --> 39:49.444
Will knows who he is.

39:49.480 --> 39:51.414
- Yes.

39:51.450 --> 39:53.816
- But our experiences shape us,
Jack.

39:56.490 --> 40:00.449
How is this experience going
to shape Will?

40:00.490 --> 40:03.493
(monitor beeping)
(ventilator pumping)

40:24.950 --> 40:26.941
(birds singing)

40:31.090 --> 40:33.979
Will Graham is troubled.

40:34.030 --> 40:36.999
- And that troubles you?

40:37.030 --> 40:40.591
Beyond a professional concern
for a patient?

40:40.630 --> 40:43.895
- I see his madness
and I want to contain it,

40:43.940 --> 40:45.908
like an oil spill.

40:45.940 --> 40:49.034
- Oil is valuable.

40:51.850 --> 40:54.819
What value does Will Graham's
madness have for you?

40:54.850 --> 40:58.616
- You're suggesting
I'm more fascinated
with the madness than the man?

40:58.650 --> 41:00.481
- Are you?

41:00.520 --> 41:02.579
- No.

41:07.530 --> 41:09.896
He realized early on
that he saw things differently

41:09.930 --> 41:13.696
than other people,
felt things differently.

41:13.730 --> 41:16.699
- So did you.

41:16.740 --> 41:19.004
- I see myself in Will.

41:19.040 --> 41:21.838
- Do you see yourself
in his madness?

41:23.840 --> 41:26.809
- Madness can be a medicine
for the modern world.

41:26.850 --> 41:29.569
You take it in moderation,
it's beneficial.

41:29.620 --> 41:32.919
- You overdose and it can have
unfortunate side effects.

41:32.950 --> 41:36.511
- Side effects can be temporary.
They can be a boost

41:36.560 --> 41:38.858
to our psychological
immune systems to help fight

41:38.890 --> 41:41.654
the existential_crises
of normal life.

41:41.700 --> 41:44.123
- Will Graham does not

41:44.160 --> 41:46.765
present you with problems
from normal life.

41:49.040 --> 41:52.009
- No. He doesn't.

41:52.040 --> 41:54.031
- What does he
present you with?

42:00.050 --> 42:02.746
- The opportunity
for friendship.

42:02.780 --> 42:05.613
- He is still your patient,
Hannibal.

42:05.650 --> 42:07.743
Where Will Graham is concerned,

42:07.790 --> 42:11.112
if you feel the impulse
to step forward,

42:11.160 --> 42:14.789
you must force yourself
to take a step back.

42:14.830 --> 42:18.766
- And just watch him
lose his mind?

42:18.800 --> 42:21.098
- Sometimes all we can do
is watch.

